{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "agentic-research-api",
    "name": "Agentic Research Assistant API",
    "description": "API collection for the Agentic Research Assistant. Set `baseUrl` and `apiKey` variables before running.\n\nAuthentication flow:\n1. Register or Login → token auto-saved to `token` variable\n2. Research endpoints use Bearer token automatically",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:3005",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "apiKey",
      "value": "your-api-key-here",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "token",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "sessionId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "jobId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "auth": {
    "type": "apikey",
    "apikey": [
      {
        "key": "key",
        "value": "x-api-key",
        "type": "string"
      },
      {
        "key": "value",
        "value": "{{apiKey}}",
        "type": "string"
      },
      {
        "key": "in",
        "value": "header",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Status",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/health/status",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "health", "status"]
            },
            "description": "Check API and database connectivity."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "User",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (body.data && body.data.token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token', body.data.token);",
                  "  }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"firstName\": \"John\",\n  \"lastName\": \"Doe\",\n  \"email\": \"john@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"securePassword123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/user/register",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "user", "register"]
            },
            "description": "Create a new user account. Password must be at least 8 characters."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (body.data && body.data.token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token', body.data.token);",
                  "    console.log('Token saved to collection variable: token');",
                  "  }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"john@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"securePassword123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Authenticate with email and password. JWT token is auto-saved to the `token` collection variable."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('token', '');",
                  "  console.log('Token cleared');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{token}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/logout",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "logout"]
            },
            "description": "Revoke the current JWT token. Clears the `token` variable on success."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Research",
      "auth": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "bearer": [
          {
            "key": "token",
            "value": "{{token}}",
            "type": "string"
          }
        ]
      },
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Sessions",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "List Sessions",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/research/sessions",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "research", "sessions"]
                },
                "description": "Retrieve all research sessions for the authenticated user, ordered by creation date descending."
              },
              "response": []
            },
            {
              "name": "Create Session",
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "exec": [
                      "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                      "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                      "  if (body.data && body.data.id) {",
                      "    pm.collectionVariables.set('sessionId', body.data.id);",
                      "    console.log('Session ID saved: ' + body.data.id);",
                      "  }",
                      "}"
                    ],
                    "type": "text/javascript"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "Content-Type",
                    "value": "application/json"
                  }
                ],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"title\": \"My Research Session\",\n  \"description\": \"Researching AI trends in 2025\",\n  \"provider\": \"openai\"\n}"
                },
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/research/sessions",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "research", "sessions"]
                },
                "description": "Create a new research session. `provider` can be `openai`, `gemini`, or `ollama`. Session ID is auto-saved to `sessionId` variable."
              },
              "response": []
            },
            {
              "name": "Get Session",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/research/sessions/{{sessionId}}",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "research", "sessions", "{{sessionId}}"]
                },
                "description": "Retrieve a specific research session by ID. Scoped to authenticated user."
              },
              "response": []
            },
            {
              "name": "Get Session Latest Job",
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "exec": [
                      "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                      "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                      "  if (body.data && body.data.jobId) {",
                      "    pm.collectionVariables.set('jobId', body.data.jobId);",
                      "    console.log('Job ID saved: ' + body.data.jobId);",
                      "  }",
                      "}"
                    ],
                    "type": "text/javascript"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/research/sessions/{{sessionId}}/jobs",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "research", "sessions", "{{sessionId}}", "jobs"]
                },
                "description": "Returns the most recent job for a session. Provides the `jobId` needed to connect to the SSE stream. Job ID is auto-saved to `jobId` variable."
              },
              "response": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Jobs",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "Submit Query",
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "exec": [
                      "if (pm.response.code === 202) {",
                      "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                      "  if (body.data && body.data.jobId) {",
                      "    pm.collectionVariables.set('jobId', body.data.jobId);",
                      "    console.log('Job ID saved: ' + body.data.jobId);",
                      "  }",
                      "}"
                    ],
                    "type": "text/javascript"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "Content-Type",
                    "value": "application/json"
                  }
                ],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"sessionId\": {{sessionId}},\n  \"query\": \"What are the latest advancements in quantum computing?\",\n  \"provider\": \"openai\"\n}"
                },
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/research/query",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "research", "query"]
                },
                "description": "Submit a research query. Returns a `jobId` immediately (202 Accepted). Poll `/jobs/:id` or connect to `/jobs/:id/stream` for progress. Job ID is auto-saved to `jobId` variable."
              },
              "response": []
            },
            {
              "name": "Get Job Status",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/research/jobs/{{jobId}}",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "research", "jobs", "{{jobId}}"]
                },
                "description": "Polling fallback to check job status and result. Checks in-memory cache first, then DB. Returns `status` and `result` (final report) when completed."
              },
              "response": []
            },
            {
              "name": "Stream Job Progress (SSE)",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "Accept",
                    "value": "text/event-stream"
                  },
                  {
                    "key": "Cache-Control",
                    "value": "no-cache"
                  }
                ],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/research/jobs/{{jobId}}/stream",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "research", "jobs", "{{jobId}}", "stream"]
                },
                "description": "Server-Sent Events (SSE) stream for real-time job progress.\n\nEvent shape:\n```json\n{ \"jobId\": \"...\", \"step\": \"retrieve|synthesize|...\", \"status\": \"started|completed|failed\", \"message\": \"...\", \"data\": {} }\n```\n\nBehavior:\n- Replays completed steps from DB on reconnect\n- Heartbeat every 15s (keeps connection alive through proxies)\n- Hard TTL of 10 minutes\n- Auto-closes on terminal events (completed/failed)\n- Reconnect directive: `retry: 1000`\n\n**Note:** Postman has limited SSE support. Use a browser or dedicated SSE client (e.g., `curl -N`) for full streaming."
              },
              "response": []
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
